<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1972,2035]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1973,1999]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species epithet is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis box="[1018,1085,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">brevis</emphasis>
”, meaning short, and “ 
<emphasis box="[1359,1420,1973,1998]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">spina</emphasis>
’, meaning spine, referring to the short gland spines on pygidium.
</paragraph>
